quran[29]{c,v,t}:
  17,70,"But We have been gracious to the children of Adam, and We have borne them by land and sea, and have provided them with good things, and have preferred them over many that We have created"
  17,71,"On the Day when We will summon all men by their record (or leaders or scriptures); and he whose book (of records) is given in his right hand shall read it (with joy), nor shall they be wronged a straw"
  17,72,"But he who in this life is blind shall be blind in the Hereafter, and err farther from the way"
  17,73,"They strove hard to beguile you from what We inspired you with, that you should invent against Us something else, and then they would have taken you for a friend"
  17,74,"And had it not been that We made you firm, you would have almost inclined towards them a little (made concessions, compromises)"
  17,75,"Then would We have made you taste of punishment of both of life and death, and you would not have found a helper against Us"
  17,76,"And they wished to scare you away from the land, to drive you forth there from; but then they would not have stayed after you except a little while"
  17,77,(This is) The way of those of Our prophets whom We have sent before you; and you shall find no change in Our way
  17,78,"Be you steadfast in prayer from the declining of the sun until the dark of the night, and the recital of the Quran at dawn; verily, the recital of the dawn is especially witnessed (or effective)"
  17,79,"And for some part of the night, watch you therein as an extra service (or for spiritual profit). It may be that your Lord will raise you to a praised (or glorious) station"
  17,80,"And say, \"O my Lord! Make my entry be by the Gate of Truth and Honour; and make my exit be likewise by the Gate of Truth and Honour; and grant me from Thee an authority to aid me"
  17,81,"And say, \"Truth has come, and falsehood has vanished! Verily, falsehood is ever bound to vanish"
  17,82,"And We will send down of the Quran that which is a healing and a mercy to the believers, though it only increases the wrong-doers in ruin"
  17,83,"And when We favour man he turns away and is averse, but when evil touches him he is in despair"
  17,84,"Say, \"Every one acts after his own manner, but your Lord is best aware of who is most guided on the way"
  17,85,"They will ask you about the Spirit. Say, \"The Spirit is (or comes) by the command of my Lord, and you are given but a little knowledge (or control) thereof"
  17,86,If We had wished We would have taken away that with which We have inspired you; then you would have found no guardian against us
  17,87,"Unless by a mercy from your Lord, verily, His grace towards you is great"
  17,88,"Say, \"If mankind and jinn united together to bring the like of this Quran, they could not produce its like, though they should help each other"
  17,89,We have displayed for mankind in this Quran all kinds of similitudes; but most of mankind refuse anything but disbelief
  17,90,"And they say, \"We will by no means believe in you, until you cause to gush forth for us a fountain from the earth"
  17,91,"Or there be made for you a garden of palms and grapes, and rivers come gushing out amidst them"
  17,92,"Or you make the sky to fall down upon us in pieces, as you have warned; or you bring us Allah and the angels before us face to face"
  17,93,"Or there be made for you a house of gold; or you climb up into the heaven; and even then We will not believe in your climbing there, until you send down on us a book that we may read!\" Say, \"Glory to my Lord! Am I aught but a mortal, a Messenge"
  17,94,"Naught prevents men from believing when the guidance came to them, save their saying, \"Has Allah sent a mortal for a messenger"
  17,95,"Say, \"Had there been on the earth settled angels walking about, then We would surely have sent them an angel as a messenger"
  17,96,"Say, \"Allah is sufficient witness between me and you; verily, He is Knower, Seer of His servants"
  17,97,"He whom Allah guides, he is indeed guided; and he whom Allah leads astray, you shall never find patrons for them beside Him; and We will assemble them on the Day of Resurrection upon their faces, blind, and dumb, and deaf; their resort is Hell; whenever i"
  17,98,"That is their reward for that they disbelieved in Our revelations, and said, \"What! When we are bones and dust, shall we then be raised up a new creation"